# NCAA Results Data Pipeline

- Build season game results from TeamRankings team pages, not third-party CSVs.
- Team list source is `ncaa-teams.xlsx` (hyperlinked TeamRankings team URLs).
- Use `npm run scrape:ncaa-results -- --start-year 2025` to generate `NCAA_Hoops_Results_2025_26.csv`.
- Required output columns are `year,month,day,team,opponent,location,teamscore,oppscore,d1`.
- `location` uses `H` (home), `V` (away), `N` (neutral).
- `d1` is `2` when opponent is D1, otherwise `1`.
- For adjusted-diff workbook cleanup, use `npm run apply:adjusted-diff-team-changes`.
- The cleanup script reads `output/team-name-changes.txt` and updates every file in `NCAA Results/Raw results/adjusted-diff-excel-files`.
- `remove` mappings delete rows where `team` or `opponent` matches the listed source team.
- To append modeling context columns, use `npm run enrich:adjusted-diff-context`.
- This enrichment script sets `season_phase` (`early`, `mid`, `late`) and `is_conference` in adjusted-diff `.xlsx` files.
- It also appends `conference` to season stats files under `multi-season-team-stats/normalized-names-results`.
- Conference source of truth for enrichment is `output/team-conferences.xlsx`, with manual team/year overrides in the enrichment script for naming and realignment edge cases.

# NCAA Team Stats Data Pipeline

- Build team-level season statistics from TeamRankings stat pages.
- Team stat catalog source: `scripts/teamrankings-ncaa-team-stat-urls.json` (all TeamRankings team stats from `https://www.teamrankings.com/ncb/stats/`).
- Regenerate catalog with Puppeteer script: `node scripts/discover-teamrankings-stat-urls-puppeteer.js`.
- Use `npm run scrape:ncaa-team-stats -- --start-year 2025` for the 2025-26 season.
- Output filename format is `NCAA_D1_Team_Stats_YYYY-YY.csv` (example: `NCAA_D1_Team_Stats_2025-26.csv`).
- Validation filename format is `NCAA_D1_Team_Stats_YYYY-YY-validation.json`.
- Metric output columns include every catalog stat key (`/ncaa-basketball/stat/...`) plus legacy aliases for backward compatibility:
  - `effective_fg_pct`, `opp_effective_fg_pct`
  - `turnover_rate`, `opp_turnover_rate`
  - `offensive_rebound_rate`
  - `free_throw_rate`, `three_point_rate`
  - `pace`
- `offensive_efficiency` and `defensive_efficiency` are converted from per-possession to per-100 possessions.
- SOS (`sos`) is sourced from TeamRankings ranking endpoint (`/ncaa-basketball/ranking/schedule-strength-by-other`) and can be backfilled into normalized master stats files with `node scripts/add-sos-to-master-stats-sos.js`.
- Build combined SOS master exports (CSV + XLSX) from season SOS files with `node scripts/build-master-sos-schedule.js`.
- Use conservative request spacing and retries to avoid TeamRankings rate-limits.
- Multi-season build default range: 2016-17 through current season via `npm run scrape:ncaa-team-stats:multi`.
- Override range with:
  - `--start-start-year=<YYYY>`
  - `--end-start-year=<YYYY>`
  - or legacy `--seasons-back=<N>`.

# Team Name Standardization Pipeline

- Standardize team names between stats and model results files before joins.
- Build mapping file with `npm run map:ncaa-team-names`.
- Apply mapping to stats file with `npm run apply:ncaa-team-names`.
- Mapping output: `team-name-map-YYYY-YY.csv` (`stats_team -> results_team`).
- Aligned stats output: `NCAA_D1_Team_Stats_YYYY-YY-results-names.csv`.
- Validation requirement: exact 365/365 overlap of team names with results file.
